 ensures that separation between two metal\nelectrodes is controlled by the insulator thickness to the molecular device\nlength scale. Here we also strongly emphasize a need for close collaboration\nbetween chemists and magnetic tunnel junction researchers. Such partnerships\nwill have a strong potential to develop magnetic tunnel junction based\nmolecular devices for the futuristic areas such as memory devices, magnetic\nmetamaterials, and high sensitivity biosensors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 6 Jul 2014 22:15:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 Dec 2019 10:37:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-04"}
