wer energy. Conclusions: The tested\nglobal \\alpha-potential is suitable at energies above 14 MeV, while a\nmodification seems necessary close to the reaction threshold. Since the \\gamma-\nand neutron width show non-negligible impact on the predictions, complementary\ndata are required to judge whether or not the discrepancies found can to be\nsolely assigned to the \\alpha-width.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Jul 2014 12:21:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-07-08"}
